def: One of the spaces between the septa in the Anthozoa.
A man who has been a slave, and has been set free.
Any one of several species of South American monkeys of thegenus Pithecia. They have large ears, and a long hairy tail which isnot prehensile.
Like the sun in form, appearance, or nature; resembling thesun. [R.] "Soliform things." Cudworth.
Fine bobbin lace made at Ypres in Belgium, usually exactly likeValenciennes lace.

A plate the film of which retains its sensitiveness only whilewet. The film used in such plates is of collodion impregnated withbromides and iodides. Before exposure the plate is immersed in asolution of silver nitrate, and immediately after exposure it isdeveloped and fixed.
One who denies the existence of the universe, or of a universeas distinct from God. G. H. Lewes.
Producing or bearing a great number; bringing forth many.
